  "debug_data_path": "debug_data/2026_331",
  "eprint": {
    "title": "Non-Trivial Zero-Knowledge Implies One-Way Functions",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Suvradip Chakraborty",
        "email": "suvchakr@visa",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "James Hulett",
        "email": "comjhulett2@illinois",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Dakshita Khurana",
        "email": "edudakshita@illinois",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Kabir Tomer",
        "email": "eduktomer2@illinois",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "A recent breakthrough [Hirahara and Nanashima, STOC’2024] established that if $\\mathsf{NP} \\not \\subseteq \\mathsf{ioP/poly}$, the existence of zero-knowledge (ZK) with negligible errors for $\\mathsf{NP}$ implies the existence of one-way functions (OWFs). This work obtains a characterization of one-way functions from the worst-case complexity of zero-knowledge in the high-error regime.\r\n\r\nAssuming $\\mathsf{NP} \\not \\subseteq \\mathsf{ioP/poly}$, we show that any non-trivial, constant-round public-coin ZK argument for NP implies the existence of OWFs, and therefore also (standard) four-message zero-knowledge arguments for $\\mathsf{NP}$. Here, we call a ZK argument non-trivial if the sum of its completeness, soundness and zero-knowledge errors is bounded away from 1.\r\n\r\nAs a special case, we also prove that non-trivial non-interactive ZK (NIZK) arguments for $\\mathsf{NP}$ imply the existence of OWFs. Using known amplification techniques, this also provides an unconditional transformation from weak to standard NIZK proofs for all meaningful error parameters. Prior work [Chakraborty, Hulett and Khurana, CRYPTO’2025] was limited to NIZKs with constant zero-knowledge error $\\varepsilon_{\\mathsf{zk}}$ and soundness error $\\varepsilon_{\\mathsf{s}}$ satisfying $\\varepsilon_{\\mathsf{zk}} + \\sqrt{\\varepsilon_{\\mathsf{s}}} < 1$.",
    "keywords": [
      "Zero Knowledge",
      "Public-Coin",
      "One-Way Functions",
      "Amplification"
    ],
    "category": "Foundations",
    "publication_info": "Preprint.",
    "last_updated": "2026-02-22",
    "license": "CC BY",
    "related_papers": []
  }
